main event: A civilian witnessed a round object in the sky for over 2 hours in Freer, Texas on March 3, 1966.
interesting points: The object was round and about the same color as a jellyfish., The object appeared to be 100' wide and 100' high., The observer first noticed the object due to a bright light outside their house., The object had no discernible means of propulsion and was silent., The sighting occurred in clear dark conditions at an altitude of 1,000' and was last seen at 15,000'.
sighted object: one round object in the sky
witness description: civilian, age 32, occupation in Freer, Texas, estimate of reliability: fair
